The paper deals with the distributed computation of first-order logic properties over graphs, which is a topic that falls under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the expressive power of first-order logic and its limitations, which are topics that fall under the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The paper uses graphs as a model for communication networks, which is a topic that falls under the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of evaluating first-order properties over graphs, which is a topic that falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
